Key Features:
Menu & Cart:

Menu items are loaded dynamically from Firebase Firestore

Users can add food items from multiple stalls to the cart

Cart updates in real time (add / remove items)

Cart data is stored in Local Storage for persistence

Cart Validation:

If the cart is empty, users cannot proceed to payment

Prevents invalid or empty orders from being created

Checkout:

Displays a summary of selected items

Optional add-ons:

Takeaway packaging

Delivery (not mandatory)

Total price updates dynamically based on selections

Multiple payment methods available (Card, NETS, Apple Pay, etc.)

Payment:

Payment process is simulated for demonstration purposes

Successful payments:

Generate a unique order ID

Save order data to Firebase Firestore

Failed payments are clearly indicated and not saved

Order History:

Retrieves all past orders from Firestore

Displays:

Order ID

Date and time

Payment method

Add-on details

Total amount

Order status (PAID / FAILED)

Expandable order view to display all items